#X obj 197 790 outlet;
#X obj 260 664 r \$0-record;
#X text 549 87 record = record mode button -> activate/deactivate automation recording;
#X text 549 168 evolvetime = sets parameter evolve time;
#X text 549 122 evolve = evolve mode button -> allows the value to be evolved to to be set and prevents parameter from updating until evolve button has been released;
#X text 549 192 jump = jump mode button -> allows the value to be jumped to to be set and prevents parameter updating until jump button has been released;
#X text 549 262 clockin = receives a bang every beat from the master clock \, which is used to trigger the start of automation playback \, ensuring that playback always starts on a beat.;
#X text 549 308 paramthrottle = receives a bang from the master parameter throttle every 10ms to control automation read back speed;
#X text 549 343 tempo = controls the speed at which the automation is read. This does skip stored values if the tempo increases \, but interpolates values if decreased.;
#X text 549 389 reverse = reverse the read back of the automation;
